⚙️ 3. Airflow Tuning Parameters Applied
The following critical environment variables and configurations were injected via Helm values.yaml to unlock the concurrency limits:
Global Limits:
AIRFLOW__CORE__PARALLELISM: [e.g., 2000] (Absolute ceiling for the cluster)
Admin -> Pools -> default_pool: [e.g., 2000 slots] (Must match or exceed parallelism)
Scheduler & K8s Optimization:
AIRFLOW__KUBERNETES_EXECUTOR__WORKER_PODS_CREATION_BATCH_SIZE: 100 (To prevent API Rate Limits while keeping high throughput)
AIRFLOW__SCHEDULER__MAX_TIS_PER_QUERY: 512
AIRFLOW__KUBERNETES_EXECUTOR__WORKER_PODS_IMAGE_PULL_POLICY: IfNotPresent (Crucial for fast Pod startup)
Test DAG Configuration:
max_active_tasks: [Target Concurrency]
Worker Pod Resources: CPU [50m], Memory [128Mi] (Lightweight sleep tasks)
Task Command: sleep 60
